# Qualtrics
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** experience management / survey software  
**Website:** [qualtrics.com](https://www.qualtrics.com)

## Overview
Qualtrics is a software-as-a-service (SaaS) company that pioneered the Experience Management (XM) category. Its platform enables organizations to collect, analyze, and act on feedback from customers, employees, and other stakeholders through surveys, dashboards, and predictive analytics. Founded in 2002, Qualtrics grew rapidly and became a leading enterprise feedback tool, serving more than 13,000 organizations globally.

In 2018, SAP acquired Qualtrics for $8 billion, the largest acquisition in SAP’s history at the time. In 2021, Qualtrics was spun out and held an independent IPO (NASDAQ: XM). The company’s success catalyzed the growth of Utah’s “Silicon Slopes” tech hub and helped establish Provo/Orem as a destination for enterprise SaaS.

## Utah connection
Qualtrics was founded in Provo, Utah, by Brigham Young University students and remains headquartered in the state. It is often cited as a flagship example of Utah’s tech ecosystem, inspiring a wave of startup formation and venture investment (e.g., Domo, Lucid, MX Technologies). Ryan Smith, Qualtrics’ co-founder and former CEO, is also a prominent Utah civic leader and owner of the Utah Jazz.

